EditorData.logicalname: Sided Nere, but killed him (Beldron prolly dead, this is edge case)

Text.Value: I've got explosive powder. That should open the way.
Leave.
There's more back there. Get them out, please!
... well. It's too late now. Thank you.
Place the powder and use fire to explode it!
Oh, thank the highest heavens. A touch of good news.

EditorData.NodeContext: GAIR-dul EYE-urn-hænd: A gnome deity. Basically, 'Thank God!'

Text.Value: Please. We have to free Beldron.
Please, just... just let me dig.

EditorData.logicalname: Said you plan to kill Philomeen

Text.Value: Gods. We've lost too many.
Beldron's still back there. Find Philomeen - and hurry!
Beldron - he's gone. And you stood there and watched.
But my Beldron is still trapped. Blow that wall open, I'm begging you.
Can't talk!
Philomeen is - gone. I thought you should know.
Get Beldron out of there. Please.
Incredible news. Drop it near the cave-in and set it alight!
Freedom - I'd forgotten how it felt. Thank you.

EditorData.logicalname: Nere and rebels are both dead

Text.Value: Thank you. For saving Beldron, I mean. I just wish...
Ironhand keep us safe.
You're no hero, no matter what the others say.
Philomeen is safe.

EditorData.logicalname: Already met Philomeen and she is alive

Text.Value: Let me be. I've got to get Beldron out of there!
Nere won't just let us go. Can't you do something?
You've done enough.

Synopsis: One-liner dialog in Ketheric City for a gnome working on the cave-in.
